Per-dimension guidance:
- BPMN_SUITABILITY: A workflow qualifies if it has trigger, ordered activities, and
  end state. Automated, technical, and operational pipelines qualify. Score low only
  when no sequenced workflow exists (e.g. static descriptions, opinions, UI specs).
- ACTORS_ROLES: Software agents, services, systems, and named components count as
  valid actors. Do not score low just because actors are non-human.
- SCOPE_CLARITY: A technical pipeline or service flow is a valid scope.
- TRACEABILITY_TO_SOURCE: Self-referential text (a document describing its own system)
  is still valid source — traceability is about evidence in the text, not externality.

